  "body": "### Scope\r\n\r\n- [x] Fix wallet tests https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/9640\r\n- [x] Track tests stability for two weeks\r\n  - To track the maintaining effort vs usefulness and decide how much effort we take in extending them or improving in any way.\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nThe few happy user workflows can catch critical broken things early in PR (like it happened recently with StatusQ layout changes and adding a new checkbox to Create Account Modal)\r\n\r\n### Action points\r\n\r\n1. Until CI stabilise PR owner will take the time to run the relevant tests locally and report in the PR if all is good and PR can be merged\r\n2. @alaibe @Khushboo-dev-cpp, @IvanBelyakoff @saledjenic @dlipicar, please comment on this issue if you encounter any problems running tests locally after they are fixed; Please report things like reason, time, effort, or instability problems ...\r\n",
